(DAH-leck)'' noun''

A fictional alien race of mutants from the British science fiction television series '''''Doctor Who''''' (first introduced in the December of 1963); the Doctor's greatest adversary, descending from the Kaled people of Skaro. 

Travel around in mechanical, tank-like casings resembling pepper shakers, with a single eyestalk on a rotating dome, gunstalk with 'death-ray', and varying robotic arm. Also genetically engineered as to remove all emotions bar hate. 

Famous catchphrases include 'Ex-ter-min-ate!' and 'I (or We) Obey!'.